      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "There's an interesting partner article to be written on this about how Wikipedia's reliance on a very narrow range of mainstream media sources ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "is",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " biasing the site, but not politically. Because the traditional media is somewhat myopic in what it covers — the sports it chooses to write about and those it doesn't, its long-term neglect of computer-gaming, even as it became a huge commercial and cultural force — Wikipedia ends up mirroring its choices. They need to start taking B2B and consumer magazines far more seriously as reliable sources. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
